ve star with a $\\sim 10^3$ au disc and envelope, is\ninstead a forming stellar association which appears to be virialized and to\nform several low-mass stars per high-mass object.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Apr 2018 18:30:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-17"}
