ic field in polar regions, which are missed in 2D surface flux transport\nmodels. This 3D model is further used to study the evolution of the magnetic\nfields due to a turbulent non-axisymmetric velocity field and to compare the\nresults with the results obtained by using a simple turbulent diffusivity\ncoefficient.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Apr 2018 10:50:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-26"}
