 streams arising from coro- nal holes near the\nsolar equator propagate in direction towards and directly hit the Earth,\nwhereas solar wind streams arising from coronal holes at higher solar latitudes\nonly graze or even miss the Earth.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Apr 2018 14:09:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 26 Apr 2018 13:12:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-27"}
